[1] Cucurbit yellow vine decline - Alabama, suspected
Date: Fri 11 Jun 2010
Source: AgFax [edited]
<http://agfax.com/Content/alabama-watermelon-curcubit-yellow-vine-06112010.aspx>


Alabama detects watermelon disease, yellow vine decline
-------------------------------------------------------
It appears we may have identified a new disease of watermelons and other
cucurbits in Alabama. On [8 Jun 2010] we collected samples from plants
expressing symptoms of "cucurbit yellow vine decline" (CYVD) from a small
commercial watermelon field in east-central Alabama.

This would be the 1st report of the disease in the state. We are trying to
confirm our diagnosis with the help of USDA [US Department of Agriculture]
scientists. The disease has been observed on squash and pumpkins, as well
as melons in the US.

Symptoms caused by CYVD are very similar to those of bacterial wilt, which
is a disease transmitted by cucumber beetles, but the progression is much
slower than CYVD, in which the plants rapidly turn yellow and wilt almost
overnight. Control of CYVD relies on managing the squash bug vectors early
in the season.

[byline: Edward Sikora]

--
